-- 
Son of VTB Head Kostin Dies in a Traffic Accident, RIA Novosti

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-07-04T08:03:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/son-of-vtb-head-kostin-dies-in-a-traffic-accident-ria-novosti.html
Andrey Kostin, a banker at Deutsche
Bank AG and the son Andrey Leonidovich Kostin, chairman and
president of VTB Group, died in a traffic accident over the
weekend, RIA Novosti reported.  Kostin, 32, died in a traffic accident in  Russia ’s Yaroslav
region, RIA said. Deutsche Bank confirmed his death, the news
service said.  Kostin, who joined Deutsche Bank in  London  in 2000, had
been a managing director in Deutsche Bank’s corporate and
investment banking division and deputy chairman of the
management board in Moscow, according to the company’s  website .  His father, also called Andrey, headed VTB Group, Russia’s
second-biggest lender, since 2002.  “We have lost not only one of the bank’s employees,”
Deutsche Bank’s Russian Chief Country Officer IgorLojevsky said
in a statement printed in Vedomosti. “We have lost one of our
closest friends.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
